1
00:00:39,290 --> 00:00:40,729
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

2
00:00:40,729 --> 00:00:42,932
(HIGH HEELS CLACKING)

3
00:00:49,170 --> 00:00:53,849
Mr. Director, this is Agent Vivian Delay.

4
00:00:53,849 --> 00:01:01,529
For the last ten years, the Central Intelligence
Agency has been after Wolfgang Braun. The Wolf.

5
00:01:01,529 --> 00:01:05,169
As you know, we have no positive
identification on what the Wolf looks like.

6
00:01:05,169 --> 00:01:08,009
What we do know is he's a
former German national

7
00:01:08,009 --> 00:01:11,489
who sells atomic material to
terrorists all over the world.

8
00:01:11,489 --> 00:01:17,969
Intelligence confirms that a transaction
is to take place next week in Belgrade.

9
00:01:17,969 --> 00:01:21,849
The Wolf's number one man, the Albino,

10
00:01:21,849 --> 00:01:24,337
will be selling a dirty
bomb to Syrian buyers.

11
00:01:25,730 --> 00:01:28,889
MAN: We have already dispatched a
team to eliminate the buyers,

12
00:01:28,889 --> 00:01:31,855
secure the bomb, and apprehend the Albino.

13
00:01:34,090 --> 00:01:36,049
How may I be of service, sir?

14
00:01:36,049 --> 00:01:38,218
Your target is the Wolf.

15
00:01:38,850 --> 00:01:41,656
We have reason to believe
he will be present.

16
00:01:42,050 --> 00:01:44,689
Find him and eliminate him.

17
00:01:44,689 --> 00:01:45,809
Yes, sir.

18
00:01:45,809 --> 00:01:49,220
Let them get the Albino,
you get the Wolf.

19
00:01:52,330 --> 00:01:58,412
Oh, sir, if I may,
who is our agent on the ground?

20
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:00,969
MAN: Ethan Renner.

21
00:02:00,969 --> 00:02:03,209
- He's a lifer.
- (COUGHING)

22
00:02:03,209 --> 00:02:05,060
He will get the job done.

23
00:02:11,170 --> 00:02:13,737
MAN:
The buyers have been neutralized.

24
00:02:13,737 --> 00:02:16,289
Well done, Ethan. Well done.

25
00:02:16,289 --> 00:02:17,980
(COMPUTERIZED VOICE) Going down.

26
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:31,571
Maid service. I have your extra towels.

27
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:54,169
ETHAN: This cold is killing me.

28
00:02:54,169 --> 00:02:56,649
- (RASPY COUGH)
- (CELL PHONE RINGS)

29
00:02:56,649 --> 00:02:58,249
- ETHAN: Yeah?
- WOMAN ON PHONE: Where are you?

30
00:02:58,249 --> 00:03:00,498
- You left a big mess.
- Yeah, well...

31
00:03:01,410 --> 00:03:04,489
I am thinking about calling in sick.

32
00:03:04,489 --> 00:03:07,580
Come on, you haven't had
a sick day in 32 years.

33
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,736
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

34
00:03:24,290 --> 00:03:26,731
- Here's the scanner.
- Thank you, Yasmin.

35
00:03:28,170 --> 00:03:33,979
Uh... be sure to stock my bedroom with
those little shampoo bottles, I like them.

36
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:37,814
All teams in position.

37
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:52,778
(PHONE ALERT JINGLES)

38
00:04:10,010 --> 00:04:11,894
Excuse me.

39
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,259
(COUGHING)

40
00:04:30,890 --> 00:04:32,330
Nice work in there, my man.

41
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:35,729
- (PHONE ALERT JINGLES)
- Oh... it's Zooey's birthday.

42
00:04:35,729 --> 00:04:37,169
I need a second to make a call.

43
00:04:37,169 --> 00:04:39,089
Cell phones aren't secure, Ethan.

44
00:04:39,089 --> 00:04:40,249
Yeah, well, it's my daughter.

45
00:04:40,249 --> 00:04:43,135
You have got a payphone outside,
you have got five minutes.

46
00:04:49,170 --> 00:04:50,371
Let's see the scan.

47
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:57,049
Hey, hey, listen I am trying to
make a phone call over there and

48
00:04:57,049 --> 00:05:00,969
I don't have any change so if I could
borrow some out of this money.

49
00:05:00,969 --> 00:05:03,970
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]
I can come back and I can pay you back.

50
00:05:05,490 --> 00:05:07,129
Come on, come on.

51
00:05:07,129 --> 00:05:08,570
Son of a bitch.

52
00:05:12,130 --> 00:05:15,289
All right, this is worth a lot.

53
00:05:15,289 --> 00:05:16,776
I take some of this.

54
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:22,215
I am coming back for that.

55
00:05:34,570 --> 00:05:36,818
Excuse me.

56
00:05:37,770 --> 00:05:39,699
Have we met before?

57
00:05:42,650 --> 00:05:44,500
You would remember me, no?

58
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:53,173
Karachi.

59
00:05:54,650 --> 00:05:57,289
Yasmin's been compromised.
We need to move now, Axel.

60
00:05:57,289 --> 00:06:02,369
No one moves on the Albino until we have
cleared what's in the box. Come on.

61
00:06:02,369 --> 00:06:06,489
Yeah, yeah, yeah. We met in
Karachi last April exactly.

62
00:06:06,489 --> 00:06:12,211
But then you were working as a cocktail
waitress if I remember it correctly?

63
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:18,329
(BEEPING)

64
00:06:18,329 --> 00:06:20,449
- Oh, shit.
- We got confirmation.

65
00:06:20,449 --> 00:06:21,856
MAN: That's a dirty bomb.

66
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:28,329
ALBINO: Boss.

67
00:06:28,729 --> 00:06:30,978
MAN: Abort.

68
00:06:34,410 --> 00:06:36,612
(LINE RINGING)

69
00:06:37,650 --> 00:06:39,898
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

70
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:50,573
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

71
00:06:56,970 --> 00:06:58,456
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

72
00:06:59,130 --> 00:07:01,569
- WOMAN ON PHONE: Hey.
- Hi sweetie, it's your father.

73
00:07:01,569 --> 00:07:04,529
You didn't forget, which
means you probably love me.

74
00:07:04,529 --> 00:07:05,929
Of course I do, Zooey.

75
00:07:05,929 --> 00:07:09,889
You can prove it by singing me
"Happy Birthday," loudly.

76
00:07:09,889 --> 00:07:14,169
Well, I could sweetheart,
but, uh, I am at work.

77
00:07:14,169 --> 00:07:15,729
You can leave a message after the beep.

78
00:07:15,729 --> 00:07:17,249
(MESSAGE BEEPS)

79
00:07:17,249 --> 00:07:18,940
What the f...?

80
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,649
All right.

81
00:07:22,649 --> 00:07:25,649
# Happy birthday to you #

82
00:07:25,649 --> 00:07:26,851
# Happy birth... #

83
00:07:27,290 --> 00:07:30,539
Go, go. Get in position. Cover me.

84
00:07:31,890 --> 00:07:33,216
- (TIRES SKID)
- # ...to you #

85
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:38,614
# Happy birthday, dear Zooey #

86
00:07:50,130 --> 00:07:52,173
(DISCONNECTED BEEPING)

87
00:07:56,170 --> 00:07:57,576
(PATRONS SCREAMING)

88
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:11,614
AXEL: Cover Ethan now.

89
00:08:13,770 --> 00:08:16,291
ETHAN:
We're going in. We're going in.

90
00:08:31,610 --> 00:08:36,054
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)
AXEL: (MUFFLED) Cover Ethan. Cover Ethan.

91
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:30,251
(EMPTY GUN CLICKING)

92
00:09:36,170 --> 00:09:37,656
(EMPTY GUN CLICKING)

93
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:56,812
(COUGHING)

94
00:10:04,130 --> 00:10:07,129
All right, that's enough.

95
00:10:07,129 --> 00:10:10,969
- Put it down.
- Put it down.

96
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,656
Now.

97
00:10:17,570 --> 00:10:18,969
Now slide it over here.

98
00:10:18,969 --> 00:10:21,049
You're not going to kill me, are you?

99
00:10:21,049 --> 00:10:23,829
Not unless I have to, all right?

100
00:10:23,829 --> 00:10:27,449
But I am not running after
you anymore, fucker.

101
00:10:27,449 --> 00:10:29,414
(SIRENS APPROACHING)

102
00:10:33,890 --> 00:10:35,694
(ERRATIC HEARTBEATING)

103
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:38,536
Ohh...

104
00:10:39,850 --> 00:10:42,178
(SHOUTS IN PAIN)

105
00:10:43,530 --> 00:10:45,529
(INDISTINCT POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

106
00:10:45,529 --> 00:10:47,858
(HELICOPTER HOVERING)

107
00:10:56,810 --> 00:10:58,978
(CHILD GIGGLING)

108
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:10,529
I see you have read the report.

109
00:11:10,529 --> 00:11:13,569
- It's called Glioblastoma.
- Yeah.

110
00:11:13,569 --> 00:11:16,809
It's a type of brain cancer and
it's spread to your lungs.

111
00:11:16,809 --> 00:11:18,978
It doesn't say how much time I have left.

112
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:23,929
Three months, possibly five.

113
00:11:23,929 --> 00:11:25,179
Yeah.

114
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:33,329
So, no Christmas this year, huh?

115
00:11:33,329 --> 00:11:35,369
I am afraid not.

116
00:11:35,369 --> 00:11:39,849
I suggest you put your affairs in order.

117
00:11:39,849 --> 00:11:41,779
MAN: Thank you, doctor.

118
00:11:43,090 --> 00:11:44,889
Well done securing the bomb, Ethan.

119
00:11:44,889 --> 00:11:48,489
But now that you're no longer operational,

120
00:11:48,489 --> 00:11:52,251
we need to terminate our relationship.

121
00:11:59,330 --> 00:12:01,809
We have wired your pension
into your account.

122
00:12:01,809 --> 00:12:04,616
The CIA thanks you for your service.

123
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:15,096
(# ANN PEEBLES "TROUBLE,
HEARTACHES, AND SADNESS" #)

124
00:13:42,690 --> 00:13:45,291
(KEYS JINGLING)

125
00:13:46,970 --> 00:13:48,171
ETHAN: What the...?

126
00:13:53,450 --> 00:13:55,652
(MAN SPEAKING MUFFLED FRENCH)

127
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:01,813
(UP-TEMPO SOUL MUSIC PLAYING IN APARTMENT)

128
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:07,054
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

129
00:14:11,330 --> 00:14:14,129
- What are you doing in my place?
- You do not speak French?

130
00:14:14,129 --> 00:14:17,061
No, I am American. I...

131
00:14:18,210 --> 00:14:19,769
- I live here.
- Which floor?

132
00:14:19,769 --> 00:14:21,529
No, I mean, I live here.

133
00:14:21,529 --> 00:14:25,329
You? You are the owner?

134
00:14:25,329 --> 00:14:27,214
I am so happy to finally meet you.

135
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:32,209
ALL: Bonjour, mon ami.

136
00:14:32,209 --> 00:14:36,249
This is my wife, Teresa.
My son Abbate.

137
00:14:36,249 --> 00:14:38,289
My daughter Sumia is in the
kitchen, she's pregnant.

138
00:14:38,289 --> 00:14:40,669
These are my cousins.
They are visiting us from Mali.

139
00:14:40,669 --> 00:14:42,829
Until they go to stay with
my brother in Saint-Denis.

140
00:14:42,829 --> 00:14:46,936
- Do you know Saint Denis?
- No, I don't know Saint Denis.

141
00:14:49,650 --> 00:14:52,529
- What are you doing in my apartment?
- We were without a home.

142
00:14:52,529 --> 00:14:55,089
We were seeking shelter.
You are lucky we're here.

143
00:14:55,089 --> 00:14:58,169
- Bad spirit fill empty spaces.
- Yeah, but now I am back.

144
00:14:58,169 --> 00:15:01,529
And it is good that you are
finally back. My name is Jules.

145
00:15:01,529 --> 00:15:03,220
Ethan.

146
00:15:05,370 --> 00:15:06,889
Where's all my stuff?

147
00:15:06,889 --> 00:15:09,849
I also started to paint the room.

148
00:15:09,849 --> 00:15:12,129
My wife think it is best
to have a cheerful color.

149
00:15:12,129 --> 00:15:15,729
Is yellow good for you? I am happy to do
the work. It's not a problem, Ethan.

150
00:15:15,729 --> 00:15:18,536
Actually, Jules, there is a problem.

151
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:22,172
(MAN SPEAKING FRENCH)

152
00:15:23,010 --> 00:15:26,929
(HEAVY FRENCH ACCENT)

153
00:15:26,929 --> 00:15:28,575
That's months from now.

154
00:15:33,210 --> 00:15:35,129
Then I guess I need to
throw them out myself.

155
00:15:35,129 --> 00:15:37,856
No, no, no, hey, ho.
(CLICKING TONGUE)

156
00:15:42,130 --> 00:15:43,369
(ALL SHOUTING IN FRENCH)

157
00:15:43,369 --> 00:15:45,569
I will go to...
Hey. I will go to jail?

158
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:46,609
[IN FRENCH]

159
00:15:46,609 --> 00:15:49,177
All right, what exactly
then am I supposed to do?

160
00:15:56,010 --> 00:15:57,929
Did you really just say that to me?

161
00:15:57,929 --> 00:16:00,736
(ALL SHOUTING)

162
00:16:01,090 --> 00:16:05,614
- (LIVELY SOUL MUSIC PLAYING)
- Ethan, Ethan.

163
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:09,609
I need to talk to your dad.

164
00:16:09,609 --> 00:16:12,289
- (JULES SPEAKING FRENCH)
- Psst.

165
00:16:12,289 --> 00:16:14,811
Please give me a minute to finish my call.

166
00:16:19,450 --> 00:16:24,816
I am sorry, Ethan.
Let's talk in private, Jules, in my room.

167
00:16:27,970 --> 00:16:30,969
I can assure you, we have not
touched any of your things.

168
00:16:30,969 --> 00:16:35,929
I am not saying you did, but
I think it's time you and I

169
00:16:35,929 --> 00:16:38,449
got to know each other
just a little better.

170
00:16:38,449 --> 00:16:43,019
Because you're not just
crashing at some guy's house.

171
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:48,421
No problem, Ethan.
We will pack and leave now.

172
00:16:48,421 --> 00:16:50,729
(JULES IN FRENCH)

173
00:16:50,729 --> 00:16:53,820
Where are you going to go
with a pregnant kid?

174
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,609
I don't know, but we will
leave without packing.

175
00:16:57,609 --> 00:16:59,141
Sit down.

176
00:17:08,890 --> 00:17:14,416
You don't have to go yet, Jules, at least...
not until your daughter has her baby.

177
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:19,429
But you stay under my rules.

178
00:17:19,429 --> 00:17:23,849
I am also a believer in rules.
Rule No. 1, no one steps in this room again.

179
00:17:23,849 --> 00:17:27,409
No one. Absolutely.
I will put a bigger sign.

180
00:17:27,409 --> 00:17:29,169
That's right, you put a bigger sign.

181
00:17:29,169 --> 00:17:33,009
Rule No. 2, you always do what
I say, no questions asked.

182
00:17:33,009 --> 00:17:35,409
Yes, of course.

183
00:17:35,409 --> 00:17:40,329
And rule No. 3, you don't
ever paint my room again.

184
00:17:40,329 --> 00:17:42,329
- You don't like the color?
- No.

185
00:17:42,329 --> 00:17:45,129
I told my wife yellow
is not a man's color.

186
00:17:45,129 --> 00:17:47,931
No, yellow is not a man's color.

187
00:17:49,490 --> 00:17:53,209
- So you also have a daughter?
- Yes.

188
00:17:53,209 --> 00:17:56,175
Like Sumia.

189
00:17:57,170 --> 00:17:58,371
(GRUNTS)

190
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:01,489
OK, OK, no more yellow.

191
00:18:01,489 --> 00:18:03,449
(SEAGULL CRIES)

192
00:18:03,449 --> 00:18:06,335
(SIRENS BLARING)

193
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:15,249
(COUGHING)

194
00:18:15,249 --> 00:18:18,889
(INDISTINCT VOICES ON TV)

195
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:20,849
WOMAN: Who is the most
beautiful girl in the world?

196
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:22,569
- Is that you?
- GIRL: Look, Daddy.

197
00:18:22,569 --> 00:18:23,849
WOMAN: That is so cute.

198
00:18:23,849 --> 00:18:25,700
(GIGGLING)

199
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:29,889
(PEACOCK TRILLING)

200
00:18:29,889 --> 00:18:31,774
WOMAN: Run, run, run.

201
00:18:45,010 --> 00:18:47,249
MAN: Hey, salut, Christine.

202
00:18:47,249 --> 00:18:49,134
Hi, you.

203
00:18:50,410 --> 00:18:52,689
(LINE RINGS)

204
00:18:52,689 --> 00:18:54,733
- (CELL PHONE RINGTONE JINGLES)
- Hey.

205
00:18:55,130 --> 00:18:56,456
[IN FRENCH]

206
00:19:01,650 --> 00:19:05,089
- This is Christine.
- ETHAN: Hello, Tina. It's me.

207
00:19:05,089 --> 00:19:06,701
I am in town.

208
00:19:09,010 --> 00:19:12,657
I am in a meeting right now, so
this is not a good time to talk.

209
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:17,329
I don't want to talk.
I want to see you.

210
00:19:17,329 --> 00:19:23,449
Yeah, I am exceptionally busy,
so, uh... unless it's urgent

211
00:19:23,449 --> 00:19:27,409
I have got some legal stuff I need you
to look at before I leave town.

212
00:19:27,409 --> 00:19:28,941
Why?

213
00:19:31,090 --> 00:19:33,729
- Are you getting married?
- No, why, are you?

214
00:19:33,729 --> 00:19:37,169
No, not today.

215
00:19:37,169 --> 00:19:40,055
All right, I will meet you outside.

216
00:19:41,170 --> 00:19:42,860
OK, see you.

217
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:47,700
(MUFFLED CHATTER)

218
00:19:52,450 --> 00:19:54,489
Why are we really here, Ethan?

219
00:19:54,489 --> 00:19:56,294
I wanted to see you.

220
00:19:59,930 --> 00:20:02,869
And our daughter, you
want to see her too?

221
00:20:02,869 --> 00:20:05,976
- Yes.
- Yes.

222
00:20:06,690 --> 00:20:09,969
I started a college fund.

223
00:20:09,969 --> 00:20:11,969
Why the sudden interest?

224
00:20:11,969 --> 00:20:15,209
It's not sudden, Tina.
I try to stay in touch.

225
00:20:15,209 --> 00:20:17,419
I left her a message on her birthday.

226
00:20:18,370 --> 00:20:22,969
Yes, and now she will have to wait
another year to hear from you again.

227
00:20:22,969 --> 00:20:24,769
I am dying, Tina.

228
00:20:24,769 --> 00:20:28,497
- You think this is easy for me?
- No, I am...

229
00:20:29,450 --> 00:20:32,381
(COUGHS) I am sick.

230
00:20:34,290 --> 00:20:36,609
I mean, I am dying.

231
00:20:36,609 --> 00:20:40,609
MAN: Sorry it took so long,
but I am afraid your will

232
00:20:40,609 --> 00:20:44,173
must be signed in both
French and English.

233
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:51,737
ETHAN: I don't want Zooey to
know, at least not right away.

234
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:00,411
Come on in.

235
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:11,409
It's nice.

236
00:21:11,409 --> 00:21:15,089
The place looks better than before.

237
00:21:15,089 --> 00:21:19,129
Don't look too hard.
It's falling apart.

238
00:21:19,129 --> 00:21:21,981
I know I haven't done
right by you and Zooey.

239
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:26,457
I want to see her before I go.

240
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:33,498
You have to make me a promise.

241
00:21:37,050 --> 00:21:39,776
I will let you see her
under one condition.

242
00:21:41,810 --> 00:21:43,171
Are you done?

243
00:21:44,170 --> 00:21:46,409
Are you really done working for them?

244
00:21:46,409 --> 00:21:49,534
- Yes.
- Promise me.

245
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:54,577
Yes. I missed a lot.

246
00:21:59,330 --> 00:22:01,689
