1261
01:43:16,490 --> 01:43:18,289
Isn't this great?

1262
01:43:18,289 --> 01:43:19,730
ETHAN: Yeah.

1263
01:43:21,290 --> 01:43:23,140
Zooey, do me a favor.

1264
01:43:24,090 --> 01:43:26,497
Try and use your best
judgment with Hugh tonight.

1265
01:43:36,570 --> 01:43:37,771
Cheers.

1266
01:43:52,010 --> 01:43:53,655
You're working again.

1267
01:43:55,330 --> 01:43:58,534
Yeah. There's a problem here.

1268
01:44:00,450 --> 01:44:03,369
That's why you came back to Paris?

1269
01:44:03,369 --> 01:44:06,849
No. I came back to see you and Zooey.

1270
01:44:06,849 --> 01:44:08,609
TINA: It was all a lie.

1271
01:44:08,609 --> 01:44:11,089
You promised you'd keep
your work away from us.

1272
01:44:11,089 --> 01:44:14,289
- You're probably not even sick.
- It's not a lie, Tina.

1273
01:44:14,289 --> 01:44:16,697
Right now I don't have
the time to explain.

1274
01:44:18,170 --> 01:44:20,054
(TINA WHIMPERS)

1275
01:44:36,450 --> 01:44:39,176
- How many guys do we have?
- (MUTTERS)

1276
01:44:42,770 --> 01:44:45,729
The police will be here in ten minutes.

1277
01:44:45,729 --> 01:44:47,969
- You all right?
- No.

1278
01:44:47,969 --> 01:44:51,140
No, I am not so good.
I have got to go...

1279
01:44:52,130 --> 01:44:54,981
If we go now, there is enough time.

1280
01:44:57,970 --> 01:45:01,174
OK. This party's over.

1281
01:45:05,370 --> 01:45:07,609
- You used us both.
- No, I would never do that.

1282
01:45:07,609 --> 01:45:09,689
I will get my funds, bring everyone in.

1283
01:45:09,689 --> 01:45:11,858
Make sure the street's blocked.

1284
01:45:13,130 --> 01:45:15,458
At least have the decency to look at me.

1285
01:45:25,530 --> 01:45:26,891
Kill him.

1286
01:45:28,570 --> 01:45:29,769
It's just bad luck.

1287
01:45:29,769 --> 01:45:31,129
(SCOFFS)

1288
01:45:31,129 --> 01:45:32,491
You're sick, Ethan.

1289
01:45:40,570 --> 01:45:43,649
Wow, this is unbelievable.

1290
01:45:43,649 --> 01:45:45,898
Yeah. I know. It's crazy.

1291
01:45:55,730 --> 01:45:57,375
I am going to be sick.

1292
01:45:58,170 --> 01:45:59,940
Come with me.

1293
01:46:07,050 --> 01:46:08,456
- (BONES CRACK)
- (YELPS)

1294
01:46:09,570 --> 01:46:11,056
(SCREAMS)

1295
01:46:17,210 --> 01:46:19,060
Did you scratch yourself?

1296
01:46:22,830 --> 01:46:24,769
No, please don't go.
Come home with me.

1297
01:46:24,769 --> 01:46:26,170
Just leave it to someone else.

1298
01:46:27,890 --> 01:46:30,092
Just please stay here.

1299
01:46:43,250 --> 01:46:44,609
- Zooey.
- What? Get down.

1300
01:46:44,609 --> 01:46:45,936
- Zooey.
- What? Get down.

1301
01:47:11,370 --> 01:47:12,571
(BEEPS)

1302
01:47:16,450 --> 01:47:18,220
You hear me in there?

1303
01:47:19,330 --> 01:47:21,055
I am sending you down.

1304
01:47:59,530 --> 01:48:01,459
(GROANING)

1305
01:48:18,610 --> 01:48:20,335
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

1306
01:48:26,770 --> 01:48:29,729
(GRUNTING)

1307
01:48:29,729 --> 01:48:32,137
(HEARTBEATS)

1308
01:48:32,930 --> 01:48:34,975
Oh, shit....

1309
01:48:40,210 --> 01:48:41,809
(CLANKING)

1310
01:48:41,809 --> 01:48:43,129
(GRUNTING)

1311
01:48:43,129 --> 01:48:44,411
Wheel's turning.

1312
01:48:48,410 --> 01:48:50,729
No, stay, you fuckers.

1313
01:48:50,729 --> 01:48:51,949
Don't....

1314
01:48:59,330 --> 01:49:01,771
(ERRATIC HEARTBEATS)

1315
01:49:06,850 --> 01:49:08,859
I got to...

1316
01:49:09,570 --> 01:49:11,454
Don't.

1317
01:49:12,170 --> 01:49:14,054
I wouldn't mind killing you.

1318
01:49:16,770 --> 01:49:18,972
You scared a lot of people up there.

1319
01:49:21,650 --> 01:49:23,818
This is my daughter's party.

1320
01:49:35,050 --> 01:49:36,581
Yes.

1321
01:49:38,410 --> 01:49:39,816
(MUTTERS)

1322
01:49:40,570 --> 01:49:41,657
Yes, come on.

1323
01:49:54,890 --> 01:49:56,376
Viv.

1324
01:49:58,970 --> 01:50:00,979
Oh, my God.

1325
01:50:04,010 --> 01:50:06,449
Am I in hell?

1326
01:50:06,449 --> 01:50:09,609
So that's what it looks
like to you, Ethan.

1327
01:50:09,609 --> 01:50:12,973
- (CHUCKLES)
- Figures.

1328
01:50:14,610 --> 01:50:17,575
- Finish it.
- What?

1329
01:50:20,050 --> 01:50:22,529
You will do what I tell you to.

1330
01:50:22,529 --> 01:50:25,939
- No.
- Finish it.

1331
01:50:26,650 --> 01:50:29,660
I passed my quota, Vivi.

1332
01:50:30,650 --> 01:50:31,809
Ethan...

1333
01:50:31,809 --> 01:50:35,059
Jesus Christ.

1334
01:50:42,810 --> 01:50:45,456
Are you really done working for them?
(GIGGLING)

1335
01:50:45,850 --> 01:50:48,649
VIVI: A killer is a killer.
He will never change.

1336
01:50:48,649 --> 01:50:50,609
I know I haven't done
right by you and Zooey.

1337
01:50:50,609 --> 01:50:52,529
VIVI: Kill him.

1338
01:50:52,529 --> 01:50:54,089
I should have left a long time ago.

1339
01:50:54,089 --> 01:50:56,369
- What about your daughter?
- I wasn't there.

1340
01:50:56,369 --> 01:50:58,489
Do... it....

1341
01:51:01,090 --> 01:51:03,549
What kind of kid doesn't
know how to ride a bike?

1342
01:51:03,549 --> 01:51:06,621
The kind of kid who never
had a father to teach her.

1343
01:51:08,730 --> 01:51:09,931
- Ethan.
- Ethan.

1344
01:51:11,250 --> 01:51:12,569
Do it.

1345
01:51:12,569 --> 01:51:14,490
ZOOEY: Promise you will
never lie to me again.

1346
01:51:15,330 --> 01:51:16,611
VIVI: You have no choice.

1347
01:51:19,490 --> 01:51:21,613
I don't think so.

1348
01:51:24,290 --> 01:51:28,017
The wife wants me to give it up.

1349
01:51:33,730 --> 01:51:35,295
(SIRENS APPROACHING)

1350
01:51:49,810 --> 01:51:52,251
(WAVES CRASHING)

1351
01:52:02,890 --> 01:52:05,172
(SEAGULL CRIES)

1352
01:52:07,330 --> 01:52:08,429
TINA: Can I talk to her?

1353
01:52:08,429 --> 01:52:11,689
ETHAN: No, she's down on the
beach right now throwing rocks.

1354
01:52:11,689 --> 01:52:14,049
- TINA: What?
- ETHAN: Yeah, we're...

1355
01:52:14,049 --> 01:52:16,089
We're taking a break from
each other right now.

1356
01:52:16,089 --> 01:52:18,289
At least she's not throwing them at me.

1357
01:52:18,289 --> 01:52:20,529
TINA: Is everything all right?

1358
01:52:20,529 --> 01:52:24,809
Yeah, it's been all right.
There's been good and bad days.

1359
01:52:24,809 --> 01:52:27,049
She said things, I have said things.

1360
01:52:27,049 --> 01:52:31,892
There's been some tears, but the week
overall's been really worth it.

1361
01:53:05,210 --> 01:53:06,411
Hey.

1362
01:53:07,650 --> 01:53:12,369
These are some presents from me and, um...
a package that was dropped at the house.

1363
01:53:12,369 --> 01:53:15,460
I can hear your car running.
Are you going to go back?

1364
01:53:21,210 --> 01:53:23,174
I love you, Tina.

1365
01:53:25,490 --> 01:53:27,499
Just not enough to quit.

1366
01:53:28,330 --> 01:53:31,932
I think you're wrong,
but I understand.

1367
01:53:34,450 --> 01:53:40,129
If I could say one word to
you to change your mind,

1368
01:53:40,129 --> 01:53:42,329
would you give me that chance?

1369
01:53:42,329 --> 01:53:43,975
This isn't a game.

1370
01:53:45,130 --> 01:53:47,529
We don't have to stay in the same room,
we don't have to sleep together,

1371
01:53:47,529 --> 01:53:50,009
that's not what I am asking.
If...

1372
01:53:50,009 --> 01:53:53,769
...that becomes important,
you will be the one to decide.

1373
01:53:53,769 --> 01:53:55,609
I will hear the music, and then I will
know. And if I never hear it...

1374
01:53:55,609 --> 01:53:57,460
I will hear the music, and then I will
know. And if I never hear it...

1375
01:53:58,890 --> 01:54:01,092
I have already gotten
more than I deserve.

1376
01:54:03,610 --> 01:54:08,896
I just want to hang out as long as
I can with my daughter and my wife.

1377
01:54:10,810 --> 01:54:13,769
What's the word? What? What's the
one word to make me change my mind?

1378
01:54:13,769 --> 01:54:15,449
What's the word? What? What's the
one word to make me change my mind?

1379
01:54:15,449 --> 01:54:19,735
It's, uh... it's Christmas.

1380
01:54:19,735 --> 01:54:22,409
(CHUCKLES)

1381
01:54:22,409 --> 01:54:24,289
That's two, Ethan.

1382
01:54:24,289 --> 01:54:26,729
- Hey, Mom.
- Hi, sweetie.

1383
01:54:26,729 --> 01:54:28,170
I am so glad you came.

1384
01:54:31,450 --> 01:54:33,175
Come on, let's go inside.

1385
01:54:34,090 --> 01:54:36,019
Dad's going to make us hot cocoa.

1386
01:54:40,730 --> 01:54:42,011
Come on.

1387
01:54:55,730 --> 01:54:58,900
(# THE TEMPER TRAP "SWEET DISPOSITION" #)

1388
01:55:03,010 --> 01:55:04,621
Is Dad a badass?

1389
01:55:06,410 --> 01:55:10,456
Well, he's, um...
He's done some things.

1390
01:55:15,810 --> 01:55:19,369
You think Dad's going to stick around?

1391
01:55:19,369 --> 01:55:21,095
As long as he can, sweetheart.

1392
01:55:23,370 --> 01:55:25,220
He loves you so much.

